text: Amy Bettina Logan (born 5 January 1985 in Auckland) is a New Zealand water polo player. She is a member of the New Zealand women's national water polo team. She played at the 2007 World Aquatics Championships, 2009 World Aquatics Championships, and 2011 World Aquatics Championships. She was educated at Epsom Girls' Grammar School. She played for the University of Hawaii's women's water polo team. == References == Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand water polo players Category:Sportspeople from Auckland
